   "source": [
    "# Unit conversion in post-processing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This feature is available from version 1.0.14."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This document shows how to use opstool to perform unit conversion.\n",
    "\n",
    "To maintain the flexibility of using OpenSeesPy, opstool implements unit conversion methods in both pre-processing and post-processing.\n",
    "\n",
    "Pre-processing: [opstool.pre.UnitSystem](https://opstool.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/api/_autosummary/opstool.pre.UnitSystem.html#opstool.pre.UnitSystem)\n",
    "\n",
    "Post-processing: [opstool.post.update_unit_system](https://opstool.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/api/_autosummary/opstool.post.update_unit_system.html#opstool.post.update_unit_system)\n",
    "\n",
    "Note that these two do not need to be run at the same time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import openseespy.opensees as ops\n",
    "\n",
    "import opstool as opst\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use the following two-dimensional truss structure:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use [Automatic Unit Conversion](https://opstool.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/pre/unit_system.html) to set the basic unit used by the model, which is the lowest level unit system. Then we can easily define the units of various physical quantities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def model(length_unit, force_unit):\n",
    "    UNIT = opst.pre.UnitSystem(length=length_unit, force=force_unit)\n",
    "    ops.wipe()\n",
    "    ops.model(\"basic\", \"-ndm\", 2, \"-ndf\", 2)\n",
    "    # create nodes\n",
    "    ops.node(1, 0, 0)\n",
    "    ops.node(2, 144.0 * UNIT.cm, 0)\n",
    "    ops.node(3, 2.0 * UNIT.m, 0)\n",
    "    ops.node(4, 80.0 * UNIT.cm, 96.0 * UNIT.cm)\n",
    "    ops.mass(4, 100 * UNIT.kg, 100 * UNIT.kg)\n",
    "    # set boundary condition\n",
    "    ops.fix(1, 1, 1)\n",
    "    ops.fix(2, 1, 1)\n",
    "    ops.fix(3, 1, 1)\n",
    "    # define materials\n",
    "    ops.uniaxialMaterial(\"Elastic\", 1, 3000.0 * UNIT.N / UNIT.cm2)\n",
    "    # define elements\n",
    "    ops.element(\"Truss\", 1, 1, 4, 100.0 * UNIT.cm2, 1)\n",
    "    ops.element(\"Truss\", 2, 2, 4, 50.0 * UNIT.cm2, 1)\n",
    "    ops.element(\"Truss\", 3, 3, 4, 50.0 * UNIT.cm2, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # create TimeSeries\n",
    "    ops.timeSeries(\"Linear\", 1)\n",
    "    ops.pattern(\"Plain\", 1, 1)\n",
    "    ops.load(4, 10.0 * UNIT.kN, -5.0 * UNIT.kN)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use ``N`` and ``mm`` as basic units"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model(length_unit=\"mm\", force_unit=\"N\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ------------------------------\n",
    "# Start of analysis generation\n",
    "# ------------------------------\n",
    "ops.system(\"BandSPD\")\n",
    "ops.numberer(\"RCM\")\n",
    "ops.constraints(\"Plain\")\n",
    "ops.integrator(\"LoadControl\", 1.0 / 10)\n",
    "ops.algorithm(\"Linear\")\n",
    "ops.analysis(\"Static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Response saving"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [

       "<span style=\"color: #2dde98; text-decoration-color: #2dde98; font-weight: bold\">g:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output/RespStepData-</span><span style=\"color: #2dde98; text-decoration-color: #2dde98; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #2dde98; text-decoration-color: #2dde98; font-weight: bold\">odb</span>!\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  All responses data with _odb_tag = \u001b[1;36m1\u001b[0m saved in \n",
       "\u001b[1;38;2;45;222;152mg:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output/RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;45;222;152m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;45;222;152modb\u001b[0m!\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "odb = opst.post.CreateODB(odb_tag=1)\n",
    "for _ in range(10):\n",
    "    ops.analyze(1)\n",
    "    odb.fetch_response_step()\n",
    "odb.save_response()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "### Unit conversion in post-processing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can now update the unit system in the post-processing. \n",
    "\n",
    "Note that ``pre`` must correspond to the base unit system selected earlier (this is a fact). \n",
    "\n",
    "``post`` is the target unit system to transform to, which can be anything. \n",
    "\n",
    "All conversions are done automatically inside opstool "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "opst.post.update_unit_system(\n",
    "    pre={\"length\": \"mm\", \"force\": \"N\"},\n",
    "    post={\"length\": \"m\", \"force\": \"kN\"},\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  Loading all response data from \u001b[1;38;2;184;69;146mg:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output/RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;184;69;146m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;184;69;146modb\u001b[0m \u001b[33m...\u001b[0m\n"
